- Average year-to-date performance is calculated by averaging the percentage values after removing the '%' symbol and converting the resulting string to a numeric value; 
- Total alerts include both active and triggered alerts; 
- If an analyst has no stocks, portfolio value, alerts, or reports, the corresponding counts will be 0.

- 'Volume Spike' refers to a significant increase in the trading volume of a stock on a given day, often indicating increased interest in the stock; 
- Portfolio valuation is the total value of all shares owned by an analyst in a particular company, calculated by multiplying the number of shares by the current price of the stock; 
- Triggered volume is the volume at which the 'Volume Spike' alert was triggered.

sql:
SELECT stock_id, date_recorded
FROM market_trends
WHERE price_change = (SELECT MAX(price_change) FROM market_trends);
